title.narrative: Multitranche Financing Facility (MFF)-Gansu Heihe Rural Hydropower Development Investment Program [(previously known as Gansu Heihe Hydropower Development Project) Project 1]

description.narrative: The Investment Program will finance the construction of 2 medium-sized hydropower plants (HPPs) in the Heihe river cascade hydropower development scheme. The Investmant Program's main impact will be to provide environmentally clean power supply in rural areas of the Gansu Province.

title.narrative: Reports and Recommendations of the President
Reports and Recommendations of the President
35 kV and 10 kV rural power grid renovated in five counties in Zhangye City by December 2009.
50.5 MW incremental hydropower capacity was added in April 2008. The project generated 197.7 GWh in 2009 and 192.1 GWh in 2010.
Erlongshan Hydropower Project was successfully registered at the UN Executive Board as a clean development mechanism project in November 2006.
On-the-job training to mainstream environmental and social issues in project development design and implementation all done by 2007.
